commitResults.messageTitle: Add basic greetings to the program
Add functionalities for the skeletal version of Duke in Level 1
Add the ability to store tasks and display to the user when requested

Add the ability to mark tasks as done. Add classes: * Task: to represent an individual task * TaskList: to represent the task list of the user Make changes to the original code to adapt to the changes. To-do: Fixing errors in corner cases, bug squashing
Add support for the three types of tasks, refractor code
Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of Duke
Add additional test for exit feature of the app
Add javadocs to new classes of tasks

Add exceptions to Duke as well as logic to detect invalid inputs. Perform code refractoring. Improve input parsing. Instead of splitting the string by every space in the input, we first split the input into two parts separated by the first space, then for deadline and event tasks we split by their respective signal (/at, /by) Include responses in methods provided by TaskList.
Add support for deleting tasks from the list. Code adaptation to storing the task using Java collection.
